Popular transfer journalist, Fabrizio Romano has said Weston McKennie’s move from Juventus to Leeds United is done. Romano said the American international will travel to England in the next 24 hours. The American will have his medicals and sign his loan contract with the Premier League side having the option to buy him for around £29 million plus add-ons. “McKennie will travel to England in the next 24h to undergo a medical test and sign the contract as a new Leeds Utd player. “€1.2m loan fee, €33m plus add-ons as buy option, personal terms agreed. “Move confirmed,” Romano tweeted on Saturday.